
steps to use Sequelize in nodejs
 1] Install mysql2 package 
 2] Install Sequelize Package 
 3] DataBase Connection using Sequelize 
 4] Define Model=> use >sequelize.define< method to define model then export it 
 5] Import Model into main index.js File
 6] Use sequelize.sync() method to store all the model data into DataBase
 7] To insert data => Product.create method
 8] To fetch/retrieve all data from database => Product.findAll method 
 
